<i>♪♪ [theme]</i>

00:02.836 --> 00:05.736
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:05.738 --> 00:08.106
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:08.108 --> 00:10.408
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:10.410 --> 00:12.177
<i>♪ Heroes in a half shell ♪</i>

00:12.179 --> 00:13.445
<i>♪ Turtle power ♪</i>

00:13.447 --> 00:14.445
<i>♪ They're the world's ♪</i>

00:14.447 --> 00:16.280
<i>♪ Most fearsome</i>
<i>fighting team ♪</i>

00:16.282 --> 00:18.183
We're really hip.

00:18.185 --> 00:20.485
<i>♪ They're heroes</i>
<i>in the half shell ♪</i>

00:20.487 --> 00:21.753
<i>♪ And they're green ♪</i>

00:21.755 --> 00:23.020
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>
Hey, get a grip.

00:23.022 --> 00:25.957
<i>♪ When the evil Shredder</i>
<i>attacks ♪</i>

00:25.959 --> 00:28.759
<i>♪ These Turtle boys</i>
<i>don't cut him no slack ♪</i>

00:28.761 --> 00:31.530
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:31.532 --> 00:34.098
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:34.100 --> 00:36.868
<i>♪ Splinter taught them</i>
<i>to be ninja teens ♪</i>

00:36.870 --> 00:38.937
He's a radical rat.

00:38.939 --> 00:40.171
<i>♪ Leonardo leads ♪</i>

00:40.173 --> 00:42.173
<i>♪ Donatello does machines ♪</i>

00:42.175 --> 00:44.009
That's a fact, Jack.

00:44.011 --> 00:46.645
<i>♪ Raphael is cool</i>
<i>but rude ♪</i>
Gimme a break.

00:46.647 --> 00:49.714
<i>♪ Michelangelo</i>
<i>is a party dude ♪</i>

00:49.716 --> 00:51.883
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:51.885 --> 00:54.619
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:54.621 --> 00:57.255
<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:57.257 --> 00:58.723
<i>♪ Heroes in a half shell ♪</i>

00:58.725 --> 01:00.458
<i>♪ Turtle power ♪</i>

01:04.830 --> 01:08.065
Darn TV, it never works
when you need it.

01:08.067 --> 01:09.534
Hey, I offered
to fix it,

01:09.536 --> 01:11.469
but Leonardo insists
on doing it himself.

01:11.471 --> 01:13.438
That's our fearless
leader for you.

01:13.440 --> 01:15.640
I can do it,
I tell you.

01:15.642 --> 01:17.875
All I have to do
is twist this knob and--

01:17.877 --> 01:18.809
Whoa!

01:19.945 --> 01:21.346
I can't understand it.

01:21.348 --> 01:23.081
I had the right knob.

01:23.083 --> 01:25.684
But you did not have
the right attitude.

01:25.686 --> 01:29.454
The true ninja spirit must
be applied to all tasks,

01:29.456 --> 01:33.124
even repairing
a television set.

01:33.126 --> 01:35.060
<i>We're here at the</i>
<i>Japanese embassy,</i>

01:35.062 --> 01:37.361
talking with
Ambassador Murishima,

01:37.363 --> 01:40.732
who is hosting this exhibition
of historic artifacts.

01:40.734 --> 01:42.601
Can you tell us
about them, Ambassador?

01:42.603 --> 01:44.001
Gladly, Ms. O'Neil.

01:44.003 --> 01:46.738
The most priceless object
in the entire collection

01:46.740 --> 01:48.973
is this ancient,
legendary weapon.

01:48.975 --> 01:51.576
The Sword of Yurikawa.

01:51.578 --> 01:53.377
You recognize it,
sensei?

01:53.379 --> 01:54.946
How could I not?

01:54.948 --> 01:57.348
It once belonged
to my own ninja master.

01:57.350 --> 02:03.021
The Sword of Yurikawa
has the amazing power
of transformation:

02:03.023 --> 02:06.858
always changing,
yet always the same.

02:06.860 --> 02:08.826
Whoa! Time out.

02:08.828 --> 02:10.294
If something changes,

02:10.297 --> 02:13.031
then how can it,
like, stay the same?

02:13.033 --> 02:14.732
Forget it, Michelangelo.

02:14.734 --> 02:15.934
It's too deep for you.

02:15.936 --> 02:18.102
A kiddie's wading pool
is too deep for him.

02:18.104 --> 02:20.905
If such a weapon should
fall into the wrong hands,

02:20.907 --> 02:22.941
it could have dire
consequences.

02:22.943 --> 02:25.677
My students, you must
go at once to guard it.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.412
Aw, come on, sensei.

02:27.414 --> 02:29.481
Couldn't we wait
until after dinner?

02:29.483 --> 02:31.282
We're about to chow down.

02:31.284 --> 02:32.950
Yeah. Besides,
I'm sure the embassy

02:32.952 --> 02:35.020
has their own people
to guard the sword.

02:35.022 --> 02:36.387
It is obvious you turtles

02:36.389 --> 02:38.789
do not have
the true ninja spirit.

02:38.791 --> 02:39.858
[sigh]

02:39.860 --> 02:41.326
Master Splinter
is right.

02:41.328 --> 02:43.394
We don't have
the true ninja spirit.

02:43.396 --> 02:46.131
Now let's go show them
what we're made of.

02:46.133 --> 02:48.599
[all grumbling]

02:51.837 --> 02:53.437
Observe, Shredder,

02:53.439 --> 02:57.342
as I demonstrate my latest
brilliant invention:

02:57.344 --> 03:00.044
the Mind Bender Ray.

03:02.848 --> 03:04.416
Lean to the left.

03:05.484 --> 03:07.085
[Krang]
Lean to the right.

03:07.087 --> 03:09.320
Stand up, sit down,
fight, fight, fight.

03:11.190 --> 03:12.957
There you go-- ooh!

03:12.959 --> 03:14.492
You see, Shredder?

03:14.494 --> 03:16.594
Total obedience.

03:16.596 --> 03:19.531
My mind bender gives
me complete power

03:19.533 --> 03:23.835
over any mutant-like forms
with level Z brainwaves.

03:23.837 --> 03:25.136
Big deal.

03:25.138 --> 03:27.572
So you can control
anyone dumber than mud.

03:27.574 --> 03:31.176
Hey, we're as smart
as mud any day.

03:31.178 --> 03:33.211
Yeah, maybe even smarter.

03:33.213 --> 03:36.981
Observe how I intend
putting it to use.

03:36.983 --> 03:38.383
The Tri-State Bridge.

03:38.385 --> 03:39.683
Yes.

03:39.685 --> 03:41.619
Tomorrow, a truck convoy

03:41.621 --> 03:44.355
carrying a rare form
of toxic waste

03:44.357 --> 03:47.358
is scheduled
to drive across it.

03:47.360 --> 03:51.195
By blowing up the bridge
just at the right moment,

03:51.197 --> 03:53.798
the toxins will
fall into the water

03:53.800 --> 03:56.600
and combine
with the harbor sludge,

03:56.602 --> 03:59.870
creating a new race
of mud mutants,

03:59.872 --> 04:02.773
which I alone will control.

04:02.775 --> 04:04.442
Hmm.

04:04.444 --> 04:06.777
Putting toxic waste
to good use.

04:06.779 --> 04:07.778
A novel idea.

04:07.780 --> 04:09.747
Rocksteady, Beebop!

04:09.749 --> 04:11.149
Start loading the explosive

04:11.151 --> 04:13.418
so we can blow up
that bridge!

04:13.420 --> 04:14.986
And remember, Shredder,

04:14.988 --> 04:18.957
this operation requires
a hands-on approach.

04:18.959 --> 04:21.392
Something you could
never manage,

04:21.394 --> 04:23.727
seeing as how you
don't have any hands.

04:23.729 --> 04:25.229
[laughing]

04:25.231 --> 04:27.966
You never miss a shot,
do you?

04:30.236 --> 04:32.070
Why, it's April O' Neil!

04:32.072 --> 04:35.673
This fabulous exhibit will
be at the Japanese embassy

04:35.675 --> 04:37.141
for one week only.

04:37.143 --> 04:38.476
So don't fail to see--

04:38.478 --> 04:40.911
[April, Shredder]
The Sword of Yurikawa.

04:40.913 --> 04:42.813
With that
in my possession,

04:42.815 --> 04:44.815
there'll be no need
for explosives.

04:44.817 --> 04:48.386
Shredder, what are you
blathering about?

04:48.388 --> 04:50.021
There's no time
to explain.

04:50.023 --> 04:51.889
I must get
to the surface now!

04:51.891 --> 04:54.992
He's always been a sucker
for a pretty sword.

05:00.732 --> 05:04.469
<i>This is April O'Neil,</i>
<i>Channel 6 News, signing off.</i>

05:04.471 --> 05:07.338
Ah! the Sword of Yurikawa.

05:07.340 --> 05:09.807
I must make it part
of my collection.

05:09.809 --> 05:14.012
Every rare and exotic weapon
known to man is in this room.

05:14.014 --> 05:17.681
Priceless tools of combat
from throughout history,

05:17.683 --> 05:19.050
all mine.

05:19.052 --> 05:21.553
But the rarest weapon
of all,

05:21.555 --> 05:23.321
the Sword of Yurikawa,

05:23.323 --> 05:25.123
has always eluded me.

05:25.125 --> 05:27.726
Until now, that is.

05:31.130 --> 05:34.599
Let me see.
Now, which of my weapons

05:34.601 --> 05:36.368
shall I use to do the job?

05:36.370 --> 05:39.837
This calls for something
simple but maneuverable.

05:39.839 --> 05:44.442
Small, unobtrusive,
yet extremely effective.

05:44.444 --> 05:45.443
Voila!

05:45.445 --> 05:47.178
I have found it!

05:47.180 --> 05:50.114
So tasteful, so elegant.

05:50.116 --> 05:52.917
Who would ever guess
its destructive power?

05:56.254 --> 05:57.455
At last,

05:57.457 --> 05:59.156
the Sword of Yurikawa

05:59.158 --> 06:01.058
will be mine.

06:05.664 --> 06:08.399
Dudes, I have got
the major munchies.

06:08.401 --> 06:09.701
Well, forget it.

06:09.703 --> 06:11.769
We've got to get to
the Japanese Embassy.

06:11.771 --> 06:14.372
Chill, this will
only take a second.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.507
Wait, Michelangelo.
Don't!

06:18.743 --> 06:20.044
Sorry, compadres.

06:20.046 --> 06:24.315
I just can't resist an
anchovy and hot fudge pizza.

06:24.317 --> 06:26.050
You heard Master Splinter.

06:26.052 --> 06:28.919
We're supposed to use
true ninja attitude.

06:28.921 --> 06:32.022
But, dude, how can we
practice ninja silence

06:32.024 --> 06:33.758
with our stomachs growling?

06:33.760 --> 06:36.461
Yeah, Michelangelo's
got a point there.

06:36.463 --> 06:37.462
[sniffing]

06:37.464 --> 06:39.397
There is a certain
logic to his thinking.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.266
[sniffing]

06:41.268 --> 06:44.702
I suppose
it couldn't hurt.

06:44.704 --> 06:47.471
[all]
Turtles eat with honor!

